Text.Value: I don't see how that's any of your business.
The Crown that the brain is wearing.
Anything that threatens our alliance, threatens our chances of defeating the elder brain.
Does it matter? I said no.
You really don't know.
That's between me and the devil.
A blatant lie.
It was a good deal, all right?
It was Raphael.
I see.
We must press on. I will bolster your mental defences. Let us hope that allows us to regain some of our lost advantage before it finds you.
Me too.
Then we must be very careful.
The devil is like a cockroach - no matter what you do to it, it will always come back.
But it's concerning that something could intervene like that, especially when we are so close to the elder brain.
The stench of impending chaos is irresistible to them.
I turned him down.
An horrendous deal.
That is... a fair request.
Just imagine - a crown of sufficient power to dominate an elder brain atop a devil's head. You would be trading one apocalyptic event for another.
Here's an idea - you stay out of my head and I'll stay out of yours.
I'm not telling you.
So I ask again - what were the terms of the deal he offered you?
*You feel the touch of the Emperor's mind peeling at the edge of yours, trying to gain access, and succeeding.*
How interesting. No doubt he impressed upon you the need to do so.
You did?
*You feel its presence withdrawing from the fringes of your awareness.*
*You feel the touch of the Emperor's mind peeling at the edge of yours, trying to gain access.*
You're trying to deceive me. But why?
I thought I'd lost you.
Then perhaps my protection - but I was sure... never mind.
Does it matter? I turned down his offer.
Giving a devil what he wants sounds like a brilliant idea.
*Its thoughts slide into yours, turning through them like fingers, sifting for answers... which it finds.*
It was a good deal. I accepted.
How very gumptious of him.
Of course. I should have known the devil would come sniffing.
I shall respect your privacy on this occasion.
We must press on. I will bolster your mental defences and make sure this doesn't happen again.
Raphael? Well - thank you for your honesty.
I trust that you will continue to remember who is really on your side.
That's between me and Raphael.
Do you have any idea what it was?
You wouldn't dare.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: A beat. Player narrows their eyes angrily - they WOULD dare.

Text.Value: Tell me you turned him down?
I'm glad you had the sense to turn him down. But it certainly does matter.
And risk becoming enthralled to the elder brain?
There you are.
Thank you for telling me. And for rejecting him.
If it read your thoughts, it knows exactly what your intentions are. And it is already plotting counter-moves to stop you.
It was the elder brain - it was trying to take hold of me.
What were the terms of this deal?
It's concerning that something could come between us like that, especially when we are so close to the elder brain.
Glance away.
Someone must have intervened. Someone you don't want me to know about.

EditorData.NodeContext: like a detective pacing around a room reasoning to themself aloud

Text.Value: You rejected the offer.
He wants the Crown that's on the brain.
Tell me you turned him down.
He knows how to free Orpheus.
Good. I'm glad. But be careful.
And I, you.
*Again - the Emperor pries at the boundaries of your thoughts, invasive, curious.*
The means to free Orpheus.
I was absent for one moment...
You promised him THE CROWN?
Then the situation is worse than I thought.
You're the one who's always talking about trust. If you trust me, you'll stop this right now.
And now we must be doubly on our guard.
He wanted the Crown the brain is wearing, and offered me the means to free Orpheus.
Get out of my head or I'll throw the Astral Prism into the Hells.
And what did he offer you in return for bringing it to him?
Raphael.
I can understand that - there's reprieve in solitude.
I doubt this will be the last time you are approached.
He offered me a deal.
You play the fool, and you play it poorly. You know something.
Something was blocking me from hearing your thoughts.
It was nice to have a moment of peace and quiet.
You're telling the truth.
I'm just glad to have you back.
I know - I was worried.
But know that if you have jeopardised our mutual project, I will be forced to reconsider our alliance.
And what did he want with you?
Say nothing.
And what did he want in return for this knowledge?

EditorData.logicalname: LOGIC: Doesn't Know Raphael Wants Crown

Text.Value: Now come - we have an elder brain to destroy.

EditorData.NodeContext: like an adult making the boundaries clear to a child, and then rediverting their attention back to the main issue

Text.Value: If there is one thing you can be certain of, it is that the devil will come to collect.
Open your mind to it. You have nothing to hide.
I turned him down.
He offered me the means to free Orpheus in exchange for the Crown on top of the brain.
I don't know, I didn't wait to find out.
Without my protection, you cannot defeat the elder brain. You cannot even get close to it. No matter what the devil whispers in your ear.
You didn't feel it?
But that is your problem. I will not let you put our survival at risk. I have Orpheus well under control. Stay away from him.
Pretend to be clueless.

Synopsis: Emperor resumes psychic connection to player once Raphael is done with them and has offered them his deal.
